That’s the option I’ve chosen. It then proceeds to upload a file called
`export.zip` to my Dropbox, which takes another couple of minutes. I have this
sense that I’ve got a lot of data in there! In fact, I’m now wishing I’d just
Airdropped it to that dapper looking gentleman on the iMac…

Stay tuned for the next instalment, when I go spelunking into `export.zip` to
see what it contains!

